fect my Velious bracer or epic casting time :-(, but dont have extended affliction to test it.<br><br>5)  Anyone know the max on Extended Affliction?  is it 50% or 100%?<br><br>6)  is Extended affliction a random 1 - 20% increase in the DoT time or a static 20% increase for all casts?  I believe the mana conservation and affliction efficiency are random so I was not sure about this one.<br><br>7)  Is there a max to extended range.  45% 60% 75%?<br><br>I believe those are all my questions.  With all these new affects I know there will need to be lots of testing to see what effects will stack and which will not, also *how* they stack.  Thanks in advance for any help anyone can provide here. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=47458><b>Balise</b></a></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubalise.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balise</A> at: 6/9/02 8:20:43 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umissfoxfyre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Miss Foxfyre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/10/02 12:17:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26379.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://gwynhyfar.homestead.com/files/hm9.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Focus item stacking!?</span><hr size=1> In general: (Rich Waters' Q&A on Castersrealm)<br><blockquote>"Q: Can you explain how the overlapping Focus items will stack, particularly with mana reduction items?<br><br>A:When casting a spell, <b>you get the benefit of the best focus item of a given type</b>. If you cast a DoT spell and were wearing a Mana Preservation item (-10% mana cost) and an Affliction Efficency item (-25% mana cost), you would use the Affliction Efficiency item bonus.<br><br>If you had on the same gear and you cast a direct damage spell, it would use the Mana Preservation item bonus instead, since Affliction Efficiency only works with DoTs. <br><br>Focus effects of different types will work together however. If you have on a mana saving item, a spell haste item, and a duration extending item, all three of these can work on the same spell. <b>It's only items of the same focus type that don't stack.</b> <br><br>- Rich"</blockquote> <br><br><br><i>1) Does Extended Enhancement stack with our AA ability, or is that rumoured max of 50% on buff length enhancement true?</i><br><br>I don't have one of those items, so I can't answer this one.<br><br><br><i>2) Extended Enhancement works on Regeneration spells I believe, but does it work on clickable buffs and Group buffs? (I believe our AA ability works on group buffs but not clickable buffs, not positive though).</i><br><br>On the Shaman's Crucible some <a href="http://forums.interealms.com/shaman/showthread.php?s=&threadid=2340">said</a> it didn't work on group buffs. Perhaps that was fixed in the last patch. Can anyone else confirm? I have a Mana Preservation III item and it worked when I cast POTG yesterday, so I don't know why the other focus item wouldn't, but then again, consistency isn't always consistently applied. =\ On the other hand, Alan said this about the duration: "Spell duration foci affecting beneficial spells are no longer random. They now always extend the affected buffs for their maximum. (We never wanted to make it harder to time your buffs.)" <br><br><br><br></i>3) Will Affliction efficiency stack with SCM or Mana Conservation to give a >25% mana reduction?</i><br><br>The higher one wins out (Affliction Efficiency over Mana Preservation). No stacking there.<br><br><br><i>4) Does Extended Affliction work on right click dot's? I have Affliction Haste and I know the haste does not affect my Velious bracer or epic casting time :-(, but dont have extended affliction to test it.</i><br><br>Yes, if the dot is a normal spell from your spellbook like Drones of Doom. I have used my Coldain Military Wristguard with my Velious bracer. <br><br><i>5) Anyone know the max on Extended Affliction? is it 50% or 100%?</i><br><br>20%<br><br><br><i>6) is Extended affliction a random 1 - 20% increase in the DoT time or a static 20% increase for all casts? I believe the mana conservation and affliction efficiency are random so I was not sure about this one.</i><br><br>Seems variable just like Improved Healing.<br><br><br><i>7) Is there a max to extended range. 45% 60% 75%?</i><br><br>Max was supposed to be 15%, but some players <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessage?topicID=17356.topic">posted on Graffe's</a> this was slightly bugged due to the z-axis being used now in determing casting range. Others reported it's working fine.<br><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utatankawd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tatankawd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/10/02 12:50:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26379.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Focus item stacking!?</span><hr size=1> &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;<br>3) Will Affliction efficiency stack with SCM or Mana Conservation to give a &gt;25% mana reduction?<br><br>The higher one wins out (Affliction Efficiency over Mana Preservation). No stacking there<br>&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;<br><br>That's not what he's asking.<br><br>If you have a 50 spec in Conjuration, you save 3% mana per cast of WD.  If you have SCM3, you save another 10%.  If you have Affliction Efficiency, you save another 25%.<br><br>But, some people are hearing that there is a 25% cap on total mana savings per cast.<br><br>That's the question.  Does focus AE stack with anything else.  If not, then that's your 25% cap right there.<br><br>Tat <p>Tatanka WolfDancer, 60th Druid<BR>Snookims Whinzlow, 50th Enchanter<BR>Silvara Drakonsbane, 48th Druid<BR>Bigith Dwigus, 48th Warrior<BR>Logic of War, 7th Hammer</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubalise.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balise</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/10/02 6:12:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26379.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Focus item stacking!?</span><hr size=1> What Fox answered about #3 did satisfy part of the question, but yes, Tat, I was also wondering if you could get a >25% mana reduction (assuming the randoms all roll on max) if you had SCM3, spec 200, and Affliction Efficiency.  With the rumoured max 25% mana reduction on any spell I was wondering if anyone has done any testing.<br><br>Thanks for the answers so far, I totally missed the post on Casters Realm.<br><br>I will assume for now that the Extended Enhancement not working on group buffs is a mess-up on VI's part.<br><br>If what I know now is correct we should be able to stack 50% AA ability and 20% from Extended Enhancement (I think it was 20% for that focus affect) to get a total of 70% extension to our buff times.  This would affectively make NR 5 mins and 6 seconds long or a total of 1530hps healed over that time.<br><br>I will log back in soon and re-test the Affliction Haste and see if it now works on right click dot's (dod bracer).  If the Extended Affliction works with the bracer then it is only logical that the Affliction Haste should as well.  30% less cast time on that bracer would allow me to use it a bit more just to add a bit more damage but not make me stand still casting for a whole 7 seconds in a fight where every second counts.<br><br>I was also taking a look at the damage/mana ratio's of Drifting Death and Winged Death.  I just got home from work and I am too lazy to go cut and paste the numbers right now, but DD is *very* close to WD in mana/damage ratio (they both have the same timing relatively).  Because DD is level 44 and as we know focus II will work on level 44 spells.  SO if you take Coldain military wrist guard (Extended Affliction III) and Grey Flesh Gloves (Affliction Efficiency II) you can make that level 44 DoT very inexpensive to cast and it will last a while and do some significant damage.  More efficient then WD by far and tied or very close the BoR.  Of course if you are able to get an item with Affliction Efficiency III on it then WD would be the way to go, but for us non-NToV(and such armours) equiped types we most likely wont be able to.<br><br>Thanks again for all the help.<br><br> <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=47458><b>Balise</b></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufrisleafshadow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>frisleafshadow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/11/02 6:26:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26379.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Focus item stacking!?</span><hr size=1> Can anyone post where VI said 25% was the max on spell savings?  I just feel my ODS gives me more then 3% when I quad, being scm3 & spec evoc. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=65433>fris</a><blockquote type=cite><blockquote><hr>"We need to make sure everything is working properly before we can patch this stuff -Alan "<hr></blockquote></blockquote></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubalise.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balise</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/21/02 1:32:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26379.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Focus item stacking!?</span><hr size=1> I have tested the Afliction Haste III effect from my crown of falinkan(sp?) and it doesnt seem to affect the casting times on my SS bracer (drones of doom).  I have heard that it has from the boards here, but so far I have yet to see a less then 7 second cast time.<br><br>Anyone get their's to work? <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=47458><b>Balise</b></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaerillea.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerillea</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/21/02 2:30:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26379.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Focus item stacking!?</span><hr size=1> It appears that there may not be a cap on mana savings.  I'll borrow a Gem Encrusted Ring from someone later and see what results I get with and without it on. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=142925>~Aerillea Mystfyre~</a><br><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=142914>~Lyranna Lyrserus~</a><br>Cypriots of Team HLS</p><i></i></td></tr></table>